  <p>
      <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/data_field_notes/g/gl/gleason_grade_(secondary)_de.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">GLEASON_GRADE_(SECONDARY)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/attributes/g/gleason_grade_de.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">GLEASON_GRADE</xref>
 where additional grades are present.  </p>
  <p>The value is presented in the range 2-5.</p>
  <p>
Note: 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/data_field_notes/g/gl/gleason_grade_(secondary)_de.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">GLEASON_GRADE_(SECONDARY)</xref>
 records the highest grade (
    <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_biopsy">Biopsy</xref>
) or the second most extensive grade (TURP (Transurethral resection of the prostate) and radicals). If no additional grades are present, 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/data_field_notes/g/gl/gleason_grade_(primary)_de.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">GLEASON_GRADE_(PRIMARY)</xref>
 and 
    <xref href="http://www.datadictionary.nhs.uk/data_dictionary/data_field_notes/g/gl/gleason_grade_(secondary)_de.asp"
            scope="external"
            format="html">GLEASON_GRADE_(SECONDARY)</xref>
 are the same.  </p>


